nodes.text: A canary was a creature known for its delicate physiology. The avian Quor'sav species had a similarly frail constitution, which led Lando Calrissian to compare their physiology to a canary sometime between 3 BBY and 2 BBY.
The canary was mentioned in the 1983 novel Lando Calrissian and the Flamewind of Oseon, the second entry in The Lando Calrissian Adventures trilogy of novels by L. Neil Smith.
